{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'd like to talk to you today about the human brain,"},{"time":3000,"text":"which is what we do research on at the University of California."},{"time":5000,"text":"Just think about this problem for a second."},{"time":7000,"text":"Here is a lump of flesh, about three pounds,"},{"time":10000,"text":"which you can hold in the palm of your hand."},{"time":12000,"text":"But it can contemplate the vastness of interstellar space."},{"time":16000,"text":"It can contemplate the meaning of infinity,"},{"time":18000,"text":"ask questions about the meaning of its own existence,"},{"time":21000,"text":"about the nature of God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23000,"text":"And this is truly the most amazing thing in the world."},{"time":25000,"text":"It's the greatest mystery confronting human beings:"},{"time":28000,"text":"How does this all come about?"},{"time":30000,"text":"Well, the brain, as you know, is made up of neurons."},{"time":32000,"text":"We're looking at neurons here."},{"time":34000,"text":"There are 100 billion neurons in the adult human brain."},{"time":37000,"text":"And each neuron makes something like 1,000 to 10,000 contacts"},{"time":40000,"text":"with other neurons in the brain."},{"time":42000,"text":"And based on this, people have calculated"},{"time":44000,"text":"that the number of permutations and combinations of brain activity"},{"time":47000,"text":"exceeds the number of elementary particles in the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"So, how do you go about studying the brain?"},{"time":52000,"text":"One approach is to look at patients who had lesions"},{"time":54000,"text":"in different part of the brain, and study changes in their behavior."},{"time":57000,"text":"This is what I spoke about in the last TED."},{"time":59000,"text":"Today I'll talk about a different approach,"},{"time":61000,"text":"which is to put electrodes in different parts of the brain,"},{"time":63000,"text":"and actually record the activity of individual nerve cells in the brain."},{"time":67000,"text":"Sort of eavesdrop on the activity of nerve cells in the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"Now, one recent discovery that has been made"},{"time":74000,"text":"by researchers in Italy, in Parma,"},{"time":76000,"text":"by Giacomo Rizzolatti and his colleagues,"},{"time":79000,"text":"is a group of neurons called mirror neurons,"},{"time":81000,"text":"which are on the front of the brain in the frontal lobes."},{"time":84000,"text":"Now, it turns out there are neurons"},{"time":86000,"text":"which are called ordinary motor command neurons in the front of the brain,"},{"time":89000,"text":"which have been known for over 50 years."},{"time":91000,"text":"These neurons will fire when a person performs a specific action."},{"time":94000,"text":"For example, if I do that, and reach and grab an apple,"},{"time":97000,"text":"a motor command neuron in the front of my brain will fire."},{"time":101000,"text":"If I reach out and pull an object, another neuron will fire,"},{"time":104000,"text":"commanding me to pull that object."},{"time":106000,"text":"These are called motor command neurons that have been known for a long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"But what Rizzolatti found was"},{"time":110000,"text":"a subset of these neurons,"},{"time":112000,"text":"maybe about 20 percent of them, will also fire"},{"time":114000,"text":"when I'm looking at somebody else performing the same action."},{"time":117000,"text":"So, here is a neuron that fires when I reach and grab something,"},{"time":120000,"text":"but it also fires when I watch Joe reaching and grabbing something."},{"time":123000,"text":"And this is truly astonishing."},{"time":125000,"text":"Because it's as though this neuron is adopting"},{"time":127000,"text":"the other person's point of view."},{"time":129000,"text":"It's almost as though it's performing a virtual reality simulation"},{"time":133000,"text":"of the other person's action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"Now, what is the significance of these mirror neurons?"},{"time":138000,"text":"For one thing they must be involved in things like imitation and emulation."},{"time":141000,"text":"Because to imitate a complex act"},{"time":144000,"text":"requires my brain to adopt the other person's point of view."},{"time":147000,"text":"So, this is important for imitation and emulation."},{"time":149000,"text":"Well, why is that important?"},{"time":151000,"text":"Well, let's take a look at the next slide."},{"time":154000,"text":"So, how do you do imitation? Why is imitation important?"},{"time":157000,"text":"Mirror neurons and imitation, emulation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"Now, let's look at culture, the phenomenon of human culture."},{"time":163000,"text":"If you go back in time about [75,000] to 100,000 years ago,"},{"time":167000,"text":"let's look at human evolution, it turns out"},{"time":169000,"text":"that something very important happened around 75,000 years ago."},{"time":172000,"text":"And that is, there is a sudden emergence and rapid spread"},{"time":174000,"text":"of a number of skills that are unique to human beings"},{"time":177000,"text":"like tool use,"},{"time":179000,"text":"the use of fire, the use of shelters, and, of course, language,"},{"time":182000,"text":"and the ability to read somebody else's mind"},{"time":184000,"text":"and interpret that person's behavior."},{"time":186000,"text":"All of that happened relatively quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"Even though the human brain had achieved its present size"},{"time":191000,"text":"almost three or four hundred thousand years ago,"},{"time":193000,"text":"100,000 years ago all of this happened very, very quickly."},{"time":195000,"text":"And I claim that what happened was"},{"time":198000,"text":"the sudden emergence of a sophisticated mirror neuron system,"},{"time":201000,"text":"which allowed you to emulate and imitate other people's actions."},{"time":203000,"text":"So that when there was a sudden accidental discovery"},{"time":207000,"text":"by one member of the group, say the use of fire,"},{"time":210000,"text":"or a particular type of tool, instead of dying out,"},{"time":212000,"text":"this spread rapidly, horizontally across the population,"},{"time":215000,"text":"or was transmitted vertically, down the generations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"So, this made evolution suddenly Lamarckian,"},{"time":220000,"text":"instead of Darwinian."},{"time":222000,"text":"Darwinian evolution is slow; it takes hundreds of thousands of years."},{"time":225000,"text":"A polar bear, to evolve a coat,"},{"time":227000,"text":"will take thousands of generations, maybe 100,000 years."},{"time":230000,"text":"A human being, a child, can just watch its parent"},{"time":233000,"text":"kill another polar bear,"},{"time":236000,"text":"and skin it and put the skin on its body, fur on the body,"},{"time":239000,"text":"and learn it in one step. What the polar bear"},{"time":241000,"text":"took 100,000 years to learn,"},{"time":243000,"text":"it can learn in five minutes, maybe 10 minutes."},{"time":246000,"text":"And then once it's learned this it spreads"},{"time":248000,"text":"in geometric proportion across a population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"This is the basis. The imitation of complex skills"},{"time":254000,"text":"is what we call culture and is the basis of civilization."},{"time":257000,"text":"Now there is another kind of mirror neuron,"},{"time":259000,"text":"which is involved in something quite different."},{"time":261000,"text":"And that is, there are mirror neurons,"},{"time":263000,"text":"just as there are mirror neurons for action, there are mirror neurons for touch."},{"time":266000,"text":"In other words, if somebody touches me,"},{"time":268000,"text":"my hand, neuron in the somatosensory cortex"},{"time":270000,"text":"in the sensory region of the brain fires."},{"time":272000,"text":"But the same neuron, in some cases, will fire"},{"time":275000,"text":"when I simply watch another person being touched."},{"time":277000,"text":"So, it's empathizing the other person being touched."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"So, most of them will fire when I'm touched"},{"time":282000,"text":"in different locations. Different neurons for different locations."},{"time":285000,"text":"But a subset of them will fire even when I watch somebody else"},{"time":287000,"text":"being touched in the same location."},{"time":289000,"text":"So, here again you have neurons"},{"time":291000,"text":"which are enrolled in empathy."},{"time":293000,"text":"Now, the question then arises: If I simply watch another person being touched,"},{"time":296000,"text":"why do I not get confused and literally feel that touch sensation"},{"time":300000,"text":"merely by watching somebody being touched?"},{"time":302000,"text":"I mean, I empathize with that person but I don't literally feel the touch."},{"time":306000,"text":"Well, that's because you've got receptors in your skin,"},{"time":308000,"text":"touch and pain receptors, going back into your brain"},{"time":310000,"text":"and saying \"Don't worry, you're not being touched."},{"time":313000,"text":"So, empathize, by all means, with the other person,"},{"time":316000,"text":"but do not actually experience the touch,"},{"time":318000,"text":"otherwise you'll get confused and muddled.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"Okay, so there is a feedback signal"},{"time":322000,"text":"that vetoes the signal of the mirror neuron"},{"time":324000,"text":"preventing you from consciously experiencing that touch."},{"time":327000,"text":"But if you remove the arm, you simply anesthetize my arm,"},{"time":330000,"text":"so you put an injection into my arm,"},{"time":332000,"text":"anesthetize the brachial plexus, so the arm is numb,"},{"time":334000,"text":"and there is no sensations coming in,"},{"time":336000,"text":"if I now watch you being touched,"},{"time":338000,"text":"I literally feel it in my hand."},{"time":340000,"text":"In other words, you have dissolved the barrier"},{"time":342000,"text":"between you and other human beings."},{"time":344000,"text":"So, I call them Gandhi neurons, or empathy neurons."},{"time":347000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"And this is not in some abstract metaphorical sense."},{"time":351000,"text":"All that's separating you from him,"},{"time":353000,"text":"from the other person, is your skin."},{"time":355000,"text":"Remove the skin, you experience that person's touch in your mind."},{"time":359000,"text":"You've dissolved the barrier between you and other human beings."},{"time":362000,"text":"And this, of course, is the basis of much of Eastern philosophy,"},{"time":364000,"text":"and that is there is no real independent self,"},{"time":367000,"text":"aloof from other human beings, inspecting the world,"},{"time":369000,"text":"inspecting other people."},{"time":371000,"text":"You are, in fact, connected not just via Facebook and Internet,"},{"time":374000,"text":"you're actually quite literally connected by your neurons."},{"time":377000,"text":"And there is whole chains of neurons around this room, talking to each other."},{"time":380000,"text":"And there is no real distinctiveness"},{"time":382000,"text":"of your consciousness from somebody else's consciousness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"And this is not mumbo-jumbo philosophy."},{"time":386000,"text":"It emerges from our understanding of basic neuroscience."},{"time":389000,"text":"So, you have a patient with a phantom limb. If the arm has been removed"},{"time":392000,"text":"and you have a phantom, and you watch somebody else"},{"time":394000,"text":"being touched, you feel it in your phantom."},{"time":396000,"text":"Now the astonishing thing is,"},{"time":398000,"text":"if you have pain in your phantom limb, you squeeze the other person's hand,"},{"time":401000,"text":"massage the other person's hand,"},{"time":403000,"text":"that relieves the pain in your phantom hand,"},{"time":405000,"text":"almost as though the neuron"},{"time":407000,"text":"were obtaining relief from merely"},{"time":409000,"text":"watching somebody else being massaged."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"So, here you have my last slide."},{"time":414000,"text":"For the longest time people have regarded science"},{"time":416000,"text":"and humanities as being distinct."},{"time":418000,"text":"C.P. Snow spoke of the two cultures:"},{"time":421000,"text":"science on the one hand, humanities on the other;"},{"time":423000,"text":"never the twain shall meet."},{"time":425000,"text":"So, I'm saying the mirror neuron system underlies the interface"},{"time":427000,"text":"allowing you to rethink about issues like consciousness,"},{"time":430000,"text":"representation of self,"},{"time":432000,"text":"what separates you from other human beings,"},{"time":434000,"text":"what allows you to empathize with other human beings,"},{"time":436000,"text":"and also even things like the emergence of culture and civilization,"},{"time":439000,"text":"which is unique to human beings. Thank you."},{"time":441000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}